WEBVTT

00:30.816 --> 00:32.420
(HYDRAULIC BRAKES HISS)

00:32.455 --> 00:34.455
(SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)

00:54.576 --> 00:56.411
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

00:58.910 --> 01:00.811
MAN:<i> Like we</i>
<i>discussed yesterday,</i>

01:00.846 --> 01:05.783
<i>I really want you all to focus</i>
<i>on topic sentences more.</i>

01:05.818 --> 01:08.291
<i>Too many of you</i>
<i>are rushing into examples</i>

01:08.326 --> 01:09.886
<i>in your body paragraphs.</i>

01:09.921 --> 01:11.756
<i>It'd be good for everyone</i>
<i>to review</i>

01:11.791 --> 01:13.692
<i>the paragraph structure PDF</i>
<i>I sent you</i>

01:13.727 --> 01:15.232
<i>a few weeks ago.</i>

01:15.267 --> 01:18.829
<i>I know these rules</i>
<i>can feel constraining.</i>

01:18.864 --> 01:22.173
<i>But remember,</i>
<i>the point of this course</i>

01:22.208 --> 01:26.342
<i>is to learn how to write</i>
<i>clearly and persuasively.</i>

01:26.377 --> 01:29.675
<i>That's how you can</i>
<i>effectively communicate</i>
<i>your ideas.</i>

01:29.710 --> 01:30.874
(MESSAGE ALERT PINGS)

01:30.909 --> 01:32.342
(MAN CHUCKLES)

01:32.377 --> 01:35.450
<i>Chris, I imagine</i>
<i>that was supposed to be</i>
<i>a private chat</i>

01:35.485 --> 01:38.288
<i>that you sent</i>
<i>to the whole class.</i>
<i>Well done.</i>

01:38.323 --> 01:42.490
<i>And, yes, the camera</i>
<i>on my laptop</i>
<i>still doesn't work.</i>

01:42.525 --> 01:44.192
<i>Believe me,</i>
<i>you're not missing much.</i>

01:44.227 --> 01:47.330
<i>Oh, and for those of you</i>
<i>who still haven't</i>
<i>given me paper three,</i>

01:47.365 --> 01:50.234
<i>I need it by Wednesday,</i>
<i>no exceptions.</i>

01:51.303 --> 01:53.070
<i>And remember,</i>

01:53.105 --> 01:56.306
<i>-the more you revise</i>
<i>these essays, the better.</i>
<i>-</i> (WAVES CRASHING)

01:56.341 --> 01:57.868
<i>The more you change,</i>

01:57.903 --> 02:00.739
<i>chances are you'll express</i>
<i>your thoughts and ideas</i>

02:00.774 --> 02:02.378
<i>more clearly</i>
<i>and persuasively.</i>

02:03.315 --> 02:04.347
<i>All right?</i>

02:04.910 --> 02:06.382
(WAVE CRASHED LOUDLY)

02:13.358 --> 02:14.588
(MAN GRUNTS)

02:14.623 --> 02:16.293
(RAIN PATTERING)

02:20.365 --> 02:21.463
(GROANS)

02:22.598 --> 02:26.732
(HEAVY BREATHING)
(CONTINUES GRUNTING)

02:26.767 --> 02:29.240
(MEN ON VIDEO
BREATHING HEAVILY)

02:29.275 --> 02:32.309
(MAN GRUNTS)
(STROKING RAPIDLY)

02:32.344 --> 02:33.475
Oh!

02:33.510 --> 02:35.807
(GRUNTING)

02:36.579 --> 02:40.317
(GRUNTING IN PAIN)

02:40.913 --> 02:45.586
(GRUNTING LABORIOUSLY)

02:45.621 --> 02:47.621
(COUGHS, BREATHES HEAVILY)

02:49.394 --> 02:54.463
(GASPING AND COUGHING)

02:54.498 --> 02:59.402
<i>"Moby Dick...</i> (WHEEZES)
In the amazing book,
<i>Moby..."</i> (GROANS)

02:59.437 --> 03:01.437
(KNOCK AT DOOR)
Liz?

03:01.472 --> 03:02.966
(PANTS)
(KNOCKING CONTINUES)

03:03.001 --> 03:06.002
Just use your key,
(WHEEZES) open the door!

03:07.973 --> 03:09.907
(GASPS)
Oh, my God.

03:09.942 --> 03:11.942
Who are you?
(GROANS IN PAIN)

03:11.977 --> 03:15.044
Gosh, are you okay?
Should I call an ambulance?
I should call an am...

03:15.079 --> 03:17.585
(MEN PANTING)
(CONTINUES GROANING)

03:18.918 --> 03:20.291
Read this to me.
Do you have a phone?

03:20.326 --> 03:21.358
My phone's dead,
I need to...

03:21.393 --> 03:22.887
Please just read it!
Okay!

03:24.088 --> 03:25.560
(GRUNTS)
Okay.

03:25.595 --> 03:27.095
(GROANS)

03:27.130 --> 03:29.058
"In the amazing book,
<i>Moby Dick,</i> by the author,
Herman Melville,

03:29.093 --> 03:31.533
"the author recounts his story
of being at sea.

03:31.568 --> 03:33.964
"In the first part
of his book, the author,
calling himself Ishmael,

03:33.999 --> 03:35.065
"is in a small seaside town,

03:35.100 --> 03:37.869
"and he is sharing a bed
with a man named Queequeg."

03:37.904 --> 03:39.068
What is this?
Why am I reading this?

03:39.103 --> 03:41.510
I need to...
Just read any of it!

03:41.545 --> 03:43.809
"And I felt saddest of all
when I read
the boring chapters

03:43.844 --> 03:45.110
"that were only
descriptions of whales,

03:45.146 --> 03:47.417
"because I knew
that the author
was just trying to save us

03:47.452 --> 03:48.485
"from his own sad story..."

03:48.520 --> 03:50.321
(GASPING) Sad story.
"...just for a little while."

03:50.356 --> 03:51.522
Just for a little while.

03:51.557 --> 03:53.555
"This book made me think
about my own life...
(WHEEZES)

03:53.590 --> 03:55.425
"...and then it made me
feel glad for my..."

03:55.460 --> 03:57.790
(PANTING)

03:57.825 --> 04:00.496
Did that help?
(SIGHS)

04:00.531 --> 04:02.399
Look, do you have a phone?
My phone is dead.

04:02.434 --> 04:04.027
I need to call an ambulance.

04:04.062 --> 04:07.030
You need help.
I don't go to hospitals.

04:07.065 --> 04:10.000
I can't help you, I don't...
I don't go to hospitals.

04:11.410 --> 04:15.005
I am sorry, um...
You can go.

04:15.040 --> 04:16.644
Thank you
for reading that to me.

04:22.718 --> 04:23.915
Are you sure you're okay?

04:26.117 --> 04:27.820
I'm sorry, who are you?

04:29.494 --> 04:30.988
Are you acquainted
with the Gospel
of Jesus Christ?

04:31.023 --> 04:34.090
What?
I'm sharing
Christ's message of love,

04:34.125 --> 04:35.960
and I'm showing people...
(SIGHING) Oh.

04:35.995 --> 04:37.500
Think I should call my friend.

04:37.535 --> 04:40.635
She's a nurse,
she takes care of me.

04:40.670 --> 04:44.001
Yeah. Yeah, I'll go.
Sorry to bother you.
Wait.

04:45.543 --> 04:46.938
My phone fell under there,
can you...

04:50.614 --> 04:51.745
Yeah, sure.

04:54.486 --> 04:55.683
(SIGHS)

05:02.692 --> 05:03.823
(SIGHS)
Here it is.

05:03.858 --> 05:04.857
(GROANS IN PAIN)

05:08.995 --> 05:10.566
(MAN GRUNTS)

05:10.601 --> 05:12.403
Hey, listen, I don't know
what's gonna happen

05:12.438 --> 05:14.064
in the next few minutes.

05:14.099 --> 05:16.803
If you don't mind,
could you... (GRUNTS)

05:16.838 --> 05:18.937
Yeah. Yeah, of course.
Thank you.

05:20.545 --> 05:21.907
(PHONE LINE RINGING)

05:24.615 --> 05:26.846
(AUTOMATED VOICE SPEAKING)
<i>It's Liz. I'm not around.</i>
<i>Leave a message.</i>

05:29.213 --> 05:31.587
What was that thing
that you had me read to you?

05:33.118 --> 05:34.117
It's an essay.

05:34.988 --> 05:36.394
It's my job.

05:37.221 --> 05:39.562
I teach online
college courses.

05:39.597 --> 05:40.959
But why did you have me
read it to you?

05:45.229 --> 05:46.635
Because I thought
I was dying.

05:46.670 --> 05:48.868
And I wanted to hear it
one last time.

05:53.171 --> 05:54.973
(VELCRO RIPS)

05:55.008 --> 05:56.876
You should have called
an ambulance.

05:56.911 --> 05:58.911
With no health insurance?

05:58.946 --> 06:00.847
Being in debt
is better than being dead.

06:01.652 --> 06:02.651
What's wrong with you?

06:03.852 --> 06:05.687
Why is there
a missionary here?

06:06.756 --> 06:09.119
Someone left
the door unlocked.

06:09.154 --> 06:10.791
I left after
you fell asleep earlier,

06:11.959 --> 06:13.057
I must've forgotten.

06:14.830 --> 06:16.863
Good thing, too.
If I hadn't, you might have...

06:16.898 --> 06:18.227
Liz, I don't like it when you...

06:18.262 --> 06:20.471
Okay, okay.
I just hate the thought

06:20.506 --> 06:22.935
of you being sealed up
in this place
when I'm not here.

06:22.970 --> 06:25.102
(PUMPING SPHYGMOMANOMETER
BULB)
Now shut up, I'm trying to...

06:30.846 --> 06:33.044
(RELEASES PRESSURE)
(AIR HISSING)

06:34.619 --> 06:35.849
What?
Hush.

06:40.856 --> 06:41.987
Tell me what you felt.

06:42.726 --> 06:44.792
Pain, in my chest.

06:44.827 --> 06:45.925
Hard to breathe.

06:46.895 --> 06:48.059
I couldn't intake air.

06:49.293 --> 06:51.260
(RIPS VELCRO)

06:51.295 --> 06:53.933
How are you sleeping?
I'm not, really.

06:57.202 --> 06:58.542
Lean forward.

07:00.612 --> 07:01.776
(SIGHS)

07:02.713 --> 07:03.844
(MAN WHEEZES)

07:06.079 --> 07:07.749
You're wheezing.

07:07.784 --> 07:09.718
I always wheeze, Liz.

07:09.753 --> 07:10.950
You're wheezing more.

07:11.557 --> 07:12.853
Deep breath.

07:12.888 --> 07:15.493
(BREATHES DEEPLY
WITH DIFFICULTY)

07:16.859 --> 07:18.661
That hurt?

07:18.696 --> 07:19.761
What was my blood pressure?

07:21.963 --> 07:24.029
Two-hundred and thirty-eight
over 134.

07:29.938 --> 07:31.542
(CHUCKLING) Oh.

07:31.577 --> 07:32.675
Yeah. "Oh."

07:34.646 --> 07:35.645
(SIGHS)

07:36.142 --> 07:37.408
Hey, could you...

07:37.444 --> 07:39.781
I haven't been
to the bathroom all day,
I'm ready to explode.

07:52.026 --> 07:53.124
(GRUNTS)

07:54.897 --> 07:56.633
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

08:06.304 --> 08:07.941
(DRAWS CURTAIN)
(LIGHT SWITCH CLICKS)

08:15.049 --> 08:16.620
(TRASH CAN LID CLOSES)

08:16.655 --> 08:18.655
(SIGHS)

08:18.690 --> 08:20.558
(MAN GRUNTS)
LIZ: You need help in there?

08:21.627 --> 08:23.187
MAN: No, I'm fine. Sorry.

08:23.992 --> 08:25.596
What are you sorry about?

08:25.631 --> 08:28.797
I'm sorry. I don't know.
Just sorry.

08:28.832 --> 08:30.161
MISSIONARY: I should go.
LIZ: Thank you.

08:31.230 --> 08:33.230
You must be from New Life.

08:33.265 --> 08:35.100
You know Doug,
from the church council?

08:36.268 --> 08:38.004
Yeah, I think so?

08:38.039 --> 08:39.335
I'm not entirely sure.

08:39.370 --> 08:40.611
I'm sort of new here, so...

08:41.009 --> 08:42.074
He's my dad.

08:44.045 --> 08:46.276
Doug and Cindy adopted me
when I was a baby.

08:46.311 --> 08:47.849
Oh, that's great.

08:47.884 --> 08:49.785
I've never seen you there
before, but,

08:49.820 --> 08:51.083
again I'm sort of new, so...

08:51.118 --> 08:53.657
(SIGHS) Fucking hate New Life.
Oh.

08:53.692 --> 08:54.992
My dad forced me to go
when I was a kid.

08:55.027 --> 08:58.959
It was awful,
growing up with all
that "end times" bullshit.

09:00.193 --> 09:02.193
(SIGHS) You're young.

09:03.262 --> 09:04.393
Why the hell
would you want to believe

09:04.428 --> 09:05.999
that the world
is about to end?

09:07.365 --> 09:09.805
I believe that
when Christ returns,

09:09.840 --> 09:11.070
it's gonna be beautiful.

09:14.845 --> 09:15.976
Look, you can go.

09:17.441 --> 09:19.309
I know Charlie appreciates
the help,

09:19.344 --> 09:21.982
but if you're here
to convert him...

09:22.017 --> 09:23.214
Oh, we don't convert,

09:23.249 --> 09:24.215
our message
is a message of hope

09:24.250 --> 09:27.251
for people of all...
LIZ: People of all faiths.

09:27.286 --> 09:30.760
I know. You're sweet.
(CLICKS LIGHTER) But...

09:33.765 --> 09:34.864
(SIGHS)

09:34.900 --> 09:36.964
Believe me, he doesn't want
to hear about New Life.

09:38.198 --> 09:40.198
Why?

09:40.233 --> 09:41.870
Because it's caused him
a lot of pain.

09:42.906 --> 09:43.905
How?

09:47.713 --> 09:48.712
It killed his boyfriend.

09:50.441 --> 09:51.979
(TOILET FLUSHES)

09:54.412 --> 09:56.412
You're saying the church...
(SIGHS)

09:57.481 --> 10:00.020
Killed Charlie's
boyfriend, yes.

10:01.188 --> 10:03.056
And I should add that New Life

10:03.091 --> 10:05.289
has caused me a lot of pain
in my life.

10:05.324 --> 10:07.929
So, we don't need you
coming over here,

10:07.964 --> 10:10.096
especially not now,
not this week.

10:11.330 --> 10:13.000
Why?

10:13.035 --> 10:14.969
Because he probably
won't be here next week.

10:15.840 --> 10:17.268
Where's he going?

10:17.303 --> 10:19.402
I'm sorry
you had to come over, Liz.

10:20.779 --> 10:22.042
No, it's okay.

10:22.077 --> 10:24.946
I'm sorry
that I always think
I'm dying.

10:24.981 --> 10:28.114
Charlie, your blood pressure
is 238 over 134.

10:28.149 --> 10:30.215
I'm sorry.
Go to the hospital.

10:30.250 --> 10:32.019
I'm sorry.
Stop saying you're sorry.

10:32.054 --> 10:33.251
Go to the hospital.

10:34.353 --> 10:35.957
You have congestive
heart failure.

10:35.992 --> 10:37.255
If you don't go
to the hospital,

10:37.290 --> 10:38.322
you'll be dead by the weekend.

10:40.095 --> 10:41.963
(STERNLY) You will die.

10:43.967 --> 10:45.230
CHARLIE: Well, then,
I better get to work

10:45.265 --> 10:46.836
because I have a lot
of essays this week.

10:46.871 --> 10:48.299
God damn it!

10:48.334 --> 10:51.742
I know. I'm sorry,
I'm an awful person. I know.

10:53.174 --> 10:54.404
I'm sorry.

10:54.439 --> 10:55.905
(GRUNTS, PANTS)

10:55.941 --> 10:58.144
Did you still want to hear
about Christ's message
of love and salvation?

10:58.179 --> 10:59.277
No, he does not!

10:59.312 --> 11:00.311
MISSIONARY: Okay. Okay.

11:01.149 --> 11:02.148
I'll go.

11:04.383 --> 11:05.249
I still don't understand

11:05.284 --> 11:06.922
why you had me read
that essay to you.

11:08.156 --> 11:09.760
It's a really good essay.

11:12.028 --> 11:13.929
LIZ: Goodbye. (CLOSES DOOR)

11:16.197 --> 11:18.802
Charlie, you have to go
to the hospital.
This has gone way too far.

11:18.837 --> 11:22.102
And rack up tens of thousands
of dollars in hospital bills

11:22.137 --> 11:24.467
I'll never be able
to pay back, ever.

11:24.502 --> 11:26.403
This affects me too, you know?

11:29.507 --> 11:30.506
You're my friend.

11:32.213 --> 11:33.212
I know.

11:35.051 --> 11:36.083
I'm sorry.

11:36.118 --> 11:37.251
You say you're sorry
one more time,

11:37.286 --> 11:39.449
I will shove a knife
right into you,
I swear to God!

11:39.484 --> 11:41.825
Go ahead, what's it gonna do?

11:41.860 --> 11:43.321
My internal organs
are two feet in, at least.

11:46.557 --> 11:48.524
(LAUGHING)

11:50.066 --> 11:51.296
(COUGHS)

11:51.331 --> 11:52.330
(WHIMPERS PLAYFULLY)

11:59.911 --> 12:01.504
I've been telling you
this would happen.

12:01.539 --> 12:02.846
(SIGHS) I know.

12:05.444 --> 12:07.411
Haven't I been telling you?
You have.

12:17.621 --> 12:20.028
