NEWSCASTER 1:
<i>Meanwhile, Vermont senator</i>
<i>Bernie Sanders</i>

12:47.559 --> 12:50.861
<i>is expected to win</i>
<i>the Gem State</i>
<i>on the Democratic side...</i>

12:50.896 --> 12:51.762
Please.

12:51.797 --> 12:54.293
(NEWSCASTER 1 CONTINUES
INDISTINCTLY)

13:19.287 --> 13:20.286
Thank you.

13:31.662 --> 13:33.530
(CRUNCHING)

13:43.113 --> 13:45.080
(LAUGHTER ON TV)

13:45.115 --> 13:47.379
Oh, I've seen this one,
it's good.

13:47.414 --> 13:49.216
(INDISTINCT TV CHATTER)

13:53.024 --> 13:54.650
(RAIN PATTERING)

13:56.027 --> 13:58.027
(INDISTINCT TV CHATTER)

14:00.526 --> 14:02.493
(CHARLIE CHOKES, COUGHS)

14:03.364 --> 14:05.595
(COUGHING)

14:10.635 --> 14:12.074
(REMOTE CLICKS)
(TV SWITCHES OFF)

14:15.343 --> 14:16.474
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

14:19.644 --> 14:21.919
(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)

14:38.267 --> 14:42.302
CHARLIE:<i> In the first part</i>
<i>of his book, the author,</i>

14:44.273 --> 14:46.009
<i>calling himself Ishmael,</i>

14:47.045 --> 14:52.444
<i>is in a small seaside town</i>

14:54.250 --> 14:55.381
<i>and he is</i>

14:57.451 --> 15:00.716
<i>sharing a bed with a man</i>

15:02.555 --> 15:04.060
<i>named Queequeg.</i>

15:08.396 --> 15:11.397
<i>The author and Queequeg</i>
<i>go to church,</i>

15:12.400 --> 15:15.071
<i>and later,</i>
<i>they set out on a ship</i>

15:15.106 --> 15:16.567
<i>captained</i>
<i>by the pirate named</i>

15:18.340 --> 15:19.405
Ahab,

15:22.245 --> 15:24.410
who is missing a leg,

15:24.445 --> 15:27.281
and very much wants
to kill the whale

15:29.549 --> 15:31.351
which is named Moby Dick,

15:32.453 --> 15:33.584
and which is white.

15:35.060 --> 15:37.456
In the course of the book,

15:37.491 --> 15:40.096
the pirate Ahab encounters
many hardships.

15:41.264 --> 15:44.397
His entire life is set around

15:44.432 --> 15:47.037
trying to kill
a certain whale.

15:47.072 --> 15:48.731
I think this is sad

15:48.766 --> 15:49.699
(GRUNTS)

15:49.734 --> 15:53.142
because the whale
doesn't have any emotions.

15:55.311 --> 15:56.475
(GRUNTS)

15:56.774 --> 15:58.015
He's just

15:59.381 --> 16:00.710
a poor, big animal.

16:03.220 --> 16:07.684
And I feel bad
for Ahab as well

16:09.358 --> 16:10.720
(GRUNTS)

16:10.755 --> 16:16.231
...because he thinks
that his life will be better

16:16.266 --> 16:19.399
if he can just kill this whale.

16:22.602 --> 16:24.734
But in reality,

16:25.374 --> 16:26.373
(GRUNTS)

16:28.212 --> 16:29.574
it won't help him at all.

16:31.578 --> 16:34.117
This book made me think

16:35.186 --> 16:36.317
about my own life.

16:39.817 --> 16:42.290
This book made me think
about my own life.

