you fucking do.

28:09.946 --> 28:12.540
(DEVICE BEEPS)
Take another deep breath.

28:12.575 --> 28:15.246
(BREATHES DEEPLY)
(DEVICE BEEPS)

28:15.281 --> 28:16.346
Thank you.

28:18.317 --> 28:19.921
(CHARLIE EXHALES DEEPLY)

28:19.956 --> 28:22.187
(LIZ SIGHS)

28:22.222 --> 28:26.290
We're just gonna try
some different methods,
or whatever.

28:26.325 --> 28:29.931
If you refuse to go
to the hospital,
then you'll...

28:31.066 --> 28:32.131
I don't know.

28:40.240 --> 28:41.404
Where'd this come from?

28:41.439 --> 28:42.944
(DEVICE CONTINUES BEEPING)

28:46.411 --> 28:47.410
Hey.

28:50.855 --> 28:51.854
Was she here?

28:55.057 --> 28:57.057
No, I don't like this.

28:57.092 --> 28:59.224
This isn't a good idea.

28:59.259 --> 29:01.193
You know you're not supposed
to be around her.

29:02.493 --> 29:03.833
Does her mom know about this?

29:03.868 --> 29:05.263
I just wanted to see her.

29:05.298 --> 29:07.298
Mary has kept her from me
all this time.

29:07.333 --> 29:10.004
Why do you suddenly need
to see her so bad, why now?

29:10.039 --> 29:11.038
Liz.

29:14.978 --> 29:16.076
(LIZ SIGHS)

29:18.212 --> 29:20.080
Why the hell do you have
her homework, anyway?

29:20.984 --> 29:24.480
Look, I didn't plan for this.

29:24.515 --> 29:26.218
She needs some help at school,

29:26.253 --> 29:28.583
so I'm gonna help her
with a few essays.

29:28.618 --> 29:29.751
(LIZ SCOFFS)

29:29.786 --> 29:31.861
You haven't seen her
since she was eight
years old,

29:31.896 --> 29:32.994
and you're gonna
reconnect with her

29:33.029 --> 29:34.589
by doing her homework
for her?

29:34.624 --> 29:36.129
It's fine.
It's not fine.

29:39.002 --> 29:40.837
She shouldn't be around you
when you're like this.

29:42.104 --> 29:44.632
What if something happens,
what if you need help?

29:44.667 --> 29:46.172
(DEVICE BEEPING RAPIDLY)

29:46.207 --> 29:47.371
Charlie, calm down.

29:48.374 --> 29:50.044
Hey. No.
(BEEPING STOPS)

29:52.576 --> 29:54.015
Okay. Forget it, then.

29:55.315 --> 29:57.348
I'm worried about her.
Why?

30:00.089 --> 30:01.550
Oh, you're spying on her now?

30:03.290 --> 30:05.158
It doesn't look
like she has any friends.

30:09.329 --> 30:10.361
I don't think this is...

30:15.170 --> 30:17.335
(CHARLIE SCOFFS)
Come on, a dead dog?

30:23.948 --> 30:25.409
I'm worried
that she's forgotten

30:25.444 --> 30:27.279
what an amazing person she is.

30:32.517 --> 30:34.352
She's just a teenager.

30:34.387 --> 30:36.420
Everyone is insane
when they're a teenager.

30:36.455 --> 30:37.354
When I was her age,

30:37.390 --> 30:39.126
when my dad
would really piss me off...

30:41.031 --> 30:43.130
I'm just lucky
I didn't get arrested,
that's all I'll say.

30:46.531 --> 30:47.563
Point is,

30:49.567 --> 30:52.073
bringing her over here
is a bad idea.

30:52.108 --> 30:54.108
You have enough to deal with
right now, you hear me?

30:55.639 --> 30:57.276
Do not bring her
over here again.

30:58.048 --> 30:59.146
Okay.

31:00.512 --> 31:01.511
Okay.

31:06.617 --> 31:09.123
It's not like she's alone,
you know. She has her mom.

31:15.197 --> 31:17.527
LIZ: Ugh, shit.
I have to go soon.

31:19.003 --> 31:21.201
I hate these night shifts.
(UTENSILS CLACKING)

31:21.236 --> 31:25.271
It's just a steady parade
of dumb, drunk college kids.

31:25.306 --> 31:26.503
(FAUCET RUNS)

31:27.605 --> 31:29.374
(LAUGHING) Did I tell you
about this girl

31:29.409 --> 31:31.376
from a few nights ago?
(GAGS)

31:31.411 --> 31:33.983
The puke was bright purple,
I swear.

31:34.018 --> 31:36.447
(CHOKING)
(LIZ LAUGHING)

31:36.482 --> 31:37.481
I mean, what is that?

31:37.517 --> 31:40.352
Why can't these kids
just drink beer? You know.

31:41.751 --> 31:44.059
Are you choking?
(CONTINUES CHOKING)

31:44.094 --> 31:46.292
Oh, God!
Okay, lean on that arm.

31:47.064 --> 31:48.063
Lean on that arm!

31:49.033 --> 31:50.395
Okay, I need
you to rock with me.

31:51.233 --> 31:53.266
(GRUNTS)
(CHOKES)

31:53.301 --> 31:54.630
(GRUNTS)
(CHARLIE GASPS)

31:55.567 --> 31:56.599
(LIZ YELLS)

31:56.634 --> 31:59.008
(COUGHS, WHEEZES)

31:59.043 --> 32:01.703
(COUGHING, WHEEZING)

32:01.738 --> 32:03.738
(GASPING)

32:04.774 --> 32:06.411
I'm okay. (GASPS)

32:07.546 --> 32:11.350
I'm okay. (GASPS)

32:11.385 --> 32:14.023
(SHOUTS) God damn it, Charlie,
what is wrong with you?

32:14.058 --> 32:14.957
(HITS)

32:14.993 --> 32:17.191
Chew your food
like a normal human being!

32:17.226 --> 32:19.127
You could have just died
right in front of me!

32:19.162 --> 32:20.161
I'm sorry.

32:21.230 --> 32:24.132
(CHARLIE WHIMPERS AND SOBS)

32:26.235 --> 32:27.267
I'm sorry, Liz.

32:39.380 --> 32:40.412
(OBJECT CLACKS)

32:47.586 --> 32:48.717
(LIZ EXHALES)

32:55.528 --> 32:56.527
It's okay.

33:20.619 --> 33:22.751
CHARLIE: I read through
some of the posts

33:22.786 --> 33:25.721
in the class discussion forum
this morning.

33:25.756 --> 33:28.262
In particular, a post

33:28.297 --> 33:32.530
about crafting a good thesis,
and I quote,

33:32.565 --> 33:34.730
"Just pick a sentence
from the reading

33:34.765 --> 33:37.271
"and say, 'It's good,'
or some shit."

33:37.306 --> 33:40.340
Listen, at this point
in the course,

33:40.375 --> 33:43.409
I have given you
all that I can,

33:43.444 --> 33:46.775
in terms of structure,
building a thesis,

33:46.810 --> 33:48.414
paragraph organization.

33:49.615 --> 33:52.484
But if all of that isn't built

33:52.519 --> 33:55.355
on your own original ideas
and truthful analysis,

33:55.390 --> 33:56.686
it doesn't mean anything.

33:58.426 --> 34:00.624
Think about that
as you write and revise.

34:00.659 --> 34:03.297
Think about the truth
of your argument.

34:04.762 --> 34:08.731
I know this may sound silly,
but it's important.

34:10.372 --> 34:12.801
Promise, it's important.

34:16.411 --> 34:17.806
(BIRD CHIRPING)

34:32.493 --> 34:34.559
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

34:43.603 --> 34:44.635
(STRAINING)

34:45.407 --> 34:46.571
(KEY CLATTERS)

34:53.580 --> 34:56.350
(GRUNTING SOFTLY)

35:04.954 --> 35:06.228
(KEY CLACKS)

35:07.924 --> 35:09.198
(CLAW CLICKS)

35:17.538 --> 35:19.505
(MUTTERING INDISTINCTLY)

35:22.477 --> 35:23.608
(SIGHS)

35:31.882 --> 35:34.520
This is... (EXHALES)

35:34.555 --> 35:37.193
You say that Walt Whitman
wrote<i> Song for Myself.</i>

35:37.525 --> 35:38.722
Yeah?

35:38.757 --> 35:40.493
It's called<i> Song of Myself.</i>

35:42.332 --> 35:43.364
My title's better.

35:45.533 --> 35:46.532
Yeah.

35:47.568 --> 35:48.567
Well...

35:49.504 --> 35:50.536
Okay, I'll just change it.

35:52.342 --> 35:54.705
"The poem<i> Song of Myself</i>

35:54.740 --> 35:56.707
"is in a book
called<i> Leaves of Grass.</i>

35:56.742 --> 35:58.412
"It was written
by Walt Whitman

35:58.447 --> 36:00.612
"and was published in 1855.

36:00.647 --> 36:02.581
"He paid for the first
publication himself."

36:02.616 --> 36:05.617
You don't have to read it
out loud. Just rewrite it.

36:05.652 --> 36:07.685
You're supposed
to analyze the poem.

36:07.720 --> 36:09.258
This is just a list of facts.

36:09.293 --> 36:11.458
Yup. Thank you, Wikipedia.

36:13.022 --> 36:14.725
(SMACKS LIPS)

36:14.760 --> 36:16.562
You know, it's really
an amazing poem.

36:16.597 --> 36:20.368
Whitman uses the metaphor
of "I" not to refer to himself,

36:20.403 --> 36:23.965
but to explode
the very definition of self

36:24.000 --> 36:26.473
in favor of a more
all-encompassing...

36:26.508 --> 36:27.804
I really, really don't care.

36:32.481 --> 36:34.712
You know, I think
you might like it
if you actually read it.

36:35.847 --> 36:38.485
You're just like my teachers.

36:38.520 --> 36:40.883
