I'm not losing my shit
over the poem,

36:40.918 --> 36:42.357
it's because I didn't read it.

36:42.392 --> 36:43.358
I did read it.

36:43.393 --> 36:46.020
It's overwritten, and dumb,
and repetitive.

36:46.055 --> 36:48.693
And even though he thinks
his metaphor of "I" is deep,

36:48.728 --> 36:50.596
it's actually
just a bunch of bullshit.

36:50.631 --> 36:51.564
And, in reality,

36:51.599 --> 36:54.831
he's just some worthless
19th century faggot.

36:57.374 --> 36:59.803
That's an interesting
perspective.

36:59.838 --> 37:01.574
It would make
for an interesting essay.

37:03.974 --> 37:07.041
Just write that thing
about exploding
the definition of self.

37:07.076 --> 37:08.515
My English teacher
will love it.

37:13.082 --> 37:14.422
(CHARLIE SIGHS)

37:16.987 --> 37:19.823
So, how's your mom doing?
Oh, my God.

37:21.563 --> 37:23.827
Look, if you're not
gonna write
these essays for me, then...

37:23.862 --> 37:27.600
CHARLIE: Ellie,
I don't need you here
to write these essays for you.

37:27.635 --> 37:29.305
If you want to go, you can go.

37:30.638 --> 37:31.736
You can still have the money.

37:34.576 --> 37:36.906
I thought you wanted
to get to know me.
I do,

37:36.941 --> 37:38.545
but I don't want
to force you to be here.

37:40.384 --> 37:41.449
It's up to you.

37:44.982 --> 37:45.981
(PUTS BAG DOWN)

37:47.556 --> 37:48.555
She's fine.

37:49.525 --> 37:50.623
Mom. I guess.

37:51.758 --> 37:54.022
She happy?
When she drinks.

37:55.960 --> 37:58.565
You guys still live
in that duplex
over on Orchard?

37:59.667 --> 38:00.732
You don't even know
where we live?

38:03.704 --> 38:04.703
You don't stay in touch
with Mom?

38:04.739 --> 38:08.377
Yeah, I check in with her
as often as she lets me.

38:08.412 --> 38:09.840
She really only tells me
things about you.

38:10.810 --> 38:12.073
Why?

38:12.108 --> 38:13.877
Because that's all
I want to know about.

38:20.149 --> 38:21.390
When I was 11,

38:21.425 --> 38:22.787
we moved
to the other side of town,

38:23.658 --> 38:24.756
near the Walmart.

38:25.462 --> 38:26.461
Is your mother

38:27.563 --> 38:29.563
with anyone right now?
No.

38:30.434 --> 38:32.126
Why, you interested?

38:32.161 --> 38:34.733
(CHUCKLES) No, of course not.

38:42.644 --> 38:44.039
Why'd you gain
all that weight?

38:44.074 --> 38:45.340
(INHALES DEEPLY) I don't...

38:45.376 --> 38:47.614
If you're gonna
interrogate me,
I'm gonna do the same thing.

38:50.047 --> 38:51.145
Why'd you gain
all that weight?

38:55.591 --> 38:58.955
Someone close to me
passed away, and it...

38:59.793 --> 39:01.991
It had an effect on me.

39:02.026 --> 39:03.025
Your boyfriend.

39:04.160 --> 39:06.864
My partner.
Your student.

39:06.899 --> 39:09.031
He wasn't that young.
It was a night school course.

39:09.066 --> 39:10.098
ELLIE: Oh, I remember him.

39:11.640 --> 39:12.738
You had him over
for dinner once

39:12.773 --> 39:14.707
when Mom was in Montana,
visiting Grandma.

39:16.546 --> 39:17.644
You made steaks.

39:18.647 --> 39:20.141
The good kind.

39:20.176 --> 39:23.111
Better meal
than you ever made
for me or Mom.

39:23.146 --> 39:25.652
I remember hearing
you two talk
after I went to bed.

39:28.954 --> 39:30.723
How do you remember all that?

39:30.758 --> 39:33.022
I told you,
I never forget anything.

39:43.199 --> 39:44.198
How did he die?

39:46.202 --> 39:48.510
I... I don't... I'm...

39:48.545 --> 39:50.809
I really don't want
to talk about that right now,

39:52.076 --> 39:53.581
if that's all right with you.

39:58.654 --> 40:00.654
(CELL PHONE KEYS CLACKING)

40:05.221 --> 40:06.693
I'll write these essays
for you.

40:08.598 --> 40:11.764
I want you to do some writing,
just for me.

40:12.800 --> 40:14.635
I hate writing essays.

40:14.670 --> 40:16.230
Just think about the poem
for a while,

40:17.233 --> 40:18.232
and write something.

40:20.940 --> 40:22.841
Be honest.

40:22.876 --> 40:24.942
Tell me what you really think.

40:24.977 --> 40:26.680
You want me to write
what I really think?

40:28.178 --> 40:29.243
I'll be right back.

40:30.587 --> 40:32.620
Just write whatever you want.

40:35.218 --> 40:38.593
(CHARLIE GROANING
WITH EXERTION)

40:40.927 --> 40:42.025
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

40:43.160 --> 40:45.600
(CONTINUES GROANING)

40:45.635 --> 40:48.966
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

41:21.638 --> 41:23.033
(WATER RUNNING)

41:25.642 --> 41:27.741
(SUPPRESSED SOBBING)

41:28.337 --> 41:30.876
(MUFFLED SOBBING)

41:30.911 --> 41:32.746
(WATER CONTINUES RUNNING)

41:34.112 --> 41:36.585
Are you okay?

41:36.620 --> 41:38.246
Unless you're dying,
there's no way
I'm going in there.

41:38.281 --> 41:39.819
(SNIFFLES)

41:39.854 --> 41:42.085
(EXHALES) Oh, yeah.
I'm fine. I'm fine.

41:48.896 --> 41:50.698
(BRID WINGS FLAPPING)

41:58.840 --> 42:00.037
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

42:01.271 --> 42:03.041
(WATER RUNNING)
(KNOCKING CONTINUES)

42:06.914 --> 42:08.243
Hi.

42:08.278 --> 42:09.816
I was looking for Charlie?

42:10.412 --> 42:11.653
He's in the bathroom.

42:12.315 --> 42:13.721
Oh, I can come back.

42:19.124 --> 42:20.959
Are you his friend, or...

42:20.994 --> 42:22.290
I'm his daughter.

42:22.325 --> 42:24.831
Oh.
Are you surprised?

42:25.834 --> 42:26.933
Yeah, I guess.

42:26.969 --> 42:28.934
What's more surprising?
That a gay guy
has a daughter,

42:28.969 --> 42:30.606
or that someone
actually found his penis?

42:33.270 --> 42:34.269
I'm kidding.

42:35.338 --> 42:36.370
Jesus.

42:37.307 --> 42:38.506
Um...

42:38.542 --> 42:41.375
Charlie was interested
in hearing more
about my church,

42:41.410 --> 42:42.276
and I brought
some literature...

42:42.311 --> 42:44.983
Are you Mormon?
No, I'm from New Life.

42:45.018 --> 42:47.689
Oh. That end times cult thing.

42:47.724 --> 42:49.658
(POURS JUICE)
It's not a cult.

42:49.693 --> 42:51.385
Tell you one thing
that I like about religion.

42:51.420 --> 42:52.859
What I like about religion

42:52.894 --> 42:54.993
is that it assumes
that everyone is an idiot

42:55.028 --> 42:56.962
and that they're all incapable
of saving themselves.

42:56.997 --> 42:58.700
I think they got
something right with that.

42:58.735 --> 42:59.866
I don't think like that...

42:59.901 --> 43:01.736
What I don't like
about religion

43:01.771 --> 43:04.200
is that when people
accept Jesus or whatever,

43:04.235 --> 43:05.872
they suddenly think
that they're better

43:05.907 --> 43:06.973
than everyone else.
(CHARLIE GRUNTING)

43:07.008 --> 43:09.172
By accepting the fact
that they're stupid sinners,

43:09.207 --> 43:12.406
somehow they've become better,
and they turn into assholes.

43:14.982 --> 43:16.212
I don't really know
what to say.

43:16.247 --> 43:18.214
I have some pamphlets
that I think would...

43:18.249 --> 43:20.084
(CAMERA CLICKS)
Why did you just do that?

43:20.119 --> 43:21.789
Are you coming back tomorrow?

43:21.824 --> 43:23.219
I'm not sure...
Come back tomorrow.

43:23.254 --> 43:25.254
I'll be here
around the same time.

43:25.289 --> 43:26.893
I'm sorry, what's happening?

43:27.456 --> 43:28.829
(CAMERA CLICKS)

43:29.293 --> 43:30.864
Oh!

43:30.899 --> 43:32.833
Hi. I was just coming over

43:32.868 --> 43:34.032
to share these pamphlets
with you.

43:34.067 --> 43:35.165
You'll have those done
by tomorrow?

43:36.036 --> 43:37.035
Sure.

43:37.807 --> 43:39.136
Five-page minimum.

43:39.171 --> 43:40.401
It'll be good, I promise.

43:43.747 --> 43:45.340
I'm Ellie.
Thomas.

43:46.211 --> 43:48.277
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

43:49.346 --> 43:50.686
(SLAMS DOOR SHUT)

43:54.285 --> 43:55.318
So...

43:55.353 --> 43:57.924
Christ's return
has been promised
for centuries.

43:57.959 --> 43:59.321
But there are a lot
of clues in Scripture

43:59.356 --> 44:00.522
that suggest it's imminent.

44:00.557 --> 44:02.929
So, that means
we don't have time
to deny the Gospel,

44:02.964 --> 44:04.128
we don't have...
Do you really think

44:04.163 --> 44:06.361
that the world's
gonna end soon?

44:06.396 --> 44:08.363
Well, the Bible says
that no one shall know the day

44:08.398 --> 44:09.903
or the hour, but,

44:09.938 --> 44:11.366
yeah, I think we're probably
living in end times.

44:12.534 --> 44:13.940
And that doesn't bother you?

44:13.975 --> 44:15.337
No. It's the idea

44:15.372 --> 44:18.010
that a better world is coming
to replace this one.

44:18.045 --> 44:20.408
That everything terrible
about this country,

44:20.443 --> 44:22.278
this planet,
is gonna be wiped clean,

44:22.313 --> 44:25.182
and replaced with something
pure and holy, and...

44:25.217 --> 44:27.118
I'm sorry.
I don't mean to be rude,

44:27.153 --> 44:29.021
but I know all this.

44:29.826 --> 44:31.089
What do you mean?

44:31.124 --> 44:33.355
I have probably
read everything

44:33.390 --> 44:36.325
New Life Church
has ever written.

44:36.360 --> 44:39.361
Probably every pamphlet
they've ever published.

44:39.396 --> 44:41.869
Wow, that's great
and everything,

44:41.904 --> 44:43.871
but these tracts
are just the beginning.

44:43.906 --> 44:46.104
There's so much more
in the Bible that we can...
I read the Bible.

44:47.107 --> 44:48.436
Really?

44:48.471 --> 44:50.405
Sure. Couple times.

44:51.947 --> 44:53.408
Did you like it?

44:53.443 --> 44:55.949
I thought it was devastating.

44:55.984 --> 44:58.820
God creates us,
expels us from paradise.

44:58.855 --> 45:01.823
We wander around
for thousands of years
killing each other,

45:01.858 --> 45:04.859
before He comes back
and saves 144,000 of us.

45:04.894 --> 45:08.093
Meanwhile, seven-
and-a-half billion of us
fall into hell.

45:10.394 --> 45:12.427
Yeah.

45:12.462 --> 45:14.429
That's not really
how I interpret it, but...

45:16.070 --> 45:17.872
Charlie, you have
to understand,

45:18.941 --> 45:21.337
God hasn't turned
His back on you.

45:21.372 --> 45:24.208
If you accept Him,
He'll release you from this.

45:24.243 --> 45:25.572
(SIPPING)
He'll take your soul

45:25.607 --> 45:27.948
out of this body
and give you
a brand-new body.

45:27.983 --> 45:30.115
One made of pure light.
I mean, don't you want that?

45:30.150 --> 45:33.217
I'm not interested
in being saved.

45:33.252 --> 45:34.889
(SIGHS)
I appreciate what you did

45:34.924 --> 45:37.056
the other day,
but you can go.

45:37.091 --> 45:38.585
This doesn't sound
like something that I...

45:38.620 --> 45:41.357
Look, I really think
that God brought me here
for a reason.

45:41.392 --> 45:43.359
There's a reason
why I knocked on your door

45:43.394 --> 45:45.394
right when you needed
someone the most.

45:45.429 --> 45:48.430
Isn't there any way
I can help?

45:48.465 --> 45:49.564
I mean,
that's the entire reason

45:49.600 --> 45:51.598
why I became a missionary
in the first place, right?

45:51.633 --> 45:53.270
There's something
you can do for me.

45:57.507 --> 46:00.508
What?
Um, nothing I just...

46:00.543 --> 46:04.919
I hope you know
I wasn't talking about, um...

46:05.482 --> 46:07.614
What?
I'm not...

46:07.649 --> 46:09.583
Oh, my God.
I'm... I'm sorry.
I just...

46:09.618 --> 46:10.991
No.
With what
you were watching

46:11.026 --> 46:12.091
the first time
I came in here, I just...

46:12.126 --> 46:14.225
(CHUCKLES) I am not
attracted to you.

46:14.260 --> 46:17.459
Please, you gotta believe me
when I say
I'm not attracted to you.

46:17.494 --> 46:18.526
You're a fetus.

46:21.333 --> 46:22.530
I'm sorry.

46:24.204 --> 46:25.269
(SIGHS)

46:29.374 --> 46:31.374
Thomas, tell me the truth.

46:34.379 --> 46:35.477
You find me disgusting?

46:38.922 --> 46:39.921
No.

46:42.486 --> 46:43.617
I just want to help.

46:44.653 --> 46:46.554
Please, just let me help.

46:56.038 --> 46:58.302
(GRUNTS SOFTLY)

46:58.337 --> 47:00.403
Thank you.
That's very helpful.

47:07.346 --> 47:09.951
What happened to your...
Sorry. Your friend, Liz,

47:09.986 --> 47:12.415
she said
that your boyfriend,

47:12.450 --> 47:14.351
he used to go to New Life?
(DOOR OPENS)

47:16.960 --> 47:18.190
LIZ: Charlie?
Yeah.

47:19.061 --> 47:21.028
I got you this.

47:21.063 --> 47:22.524
I did some
asking around, and...

47:24.726 --> 47:26.528
What the fuck
is he doing here?

47:26.563 --> 47:28.266
He's just helping me
with something.

47:28.301 --> 47:29.630
Take it easy, Liz.

47:29.665 --> 47:32.039
Okay, well, you can go now.

47:32.470 --> 47:33.469
Liz.

47:34.637 --> 47:35.636
Go home!

47:36.980 --> 47:38.441
Sorry. I'm sorry.
Leave it.

47:38.476 --> 47:40.476
(CHARLIE GRUNTS)
I said, leave it!

47:40.511 --> 47:42.445
CHARLIE:
Liz, would you stop?

47:44.383 --> 47:47.516
Actually, stay.
We'll have a little chat.

47:51.555 --> 47:52.554
What's this?

47:54.030 --> 47:55.128
The fuck does it look like?

47:57.561 --> 47:59.561
It's a fat-guy wheelchair.

47:59.596 --> 48:01.563
And why do I need
a wheelchair?

48:01.598 --> 48:04.698
I was talking to one
of the ER doctors,

48:04.733 --> 48:08.042
He said moderate activity
would be a good idea.

48:08.077 --> 48:09.637
Sense of independence
might help you out.

48:09.672 --> 48:10.838
And what did you pay
for this thing?

48:10.873 --> 48:13.278
Nothing. We ordered it
for a patient
a few months ago.

48:13.313 --> 48:14.411
It's just been sitting around.

48:14.446 --> 48:15.478
What happened to the patient?

48:17.020 --> 48:19.053
Just try it out.

48:19.088 --> 48:20.087
Please.

48:21.123 --> 48:22.287
(SIGHS)

48:23.026 --> 48:24.652
(GRUNTING)

48:27.591 --> 48:29.294
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

48:30.330 --> 48:33.727
Beep. Beep. Beep.

48:35.566 --> 48:38.468
(LAUGHING)

48:39.603 --> 48:41.207
CHARLIE: Can I sit?
I gotcha.

48:42.408 --> 48:44.375
(CHARLIE GROANING)

48:47.050 --> 48:48.115
(CHUCKLES)

48:49.448 --> 48:51.448
Good?
Yeah, actually,
this is really nice.

48:54.090 --> 48:55.353
Yeah.

48:55.388 --> 48:57.091
Let me clear
some space for you.

48:57.654 --> 48:58.653
CHARLIE: Whee.

49:00.261 --> 49:01.260
Hello?

49:06.399 --> 49:07.530
CHARLIE: Look, no hands.

49:09.501 --> 49:11.435
Thank you, Liz.
This is great, so great.

49:11.470 --> 49:14.669
(CHUCKLES) See? I told you.
CHARLIE: I know.

49:14.704 --> 49:16.440
I should go.
Ah-pap-pap.

49:16.475 --> 49:17.672
Not until we have
our little chat.

49:19.148 --> 49:20.675
What?
LIZ: Come on.

49:27.387 --> 49:28.518
Liz.

49:28.553 --> 49:30.157
Just gimme a minute with him.

49:39.861 --> 49:41.432
(DOG BARKS IN DISTANCE)

49:57.681 --> 49:58.680
Where are you from?

50:00.189 --> 50:01.222
What?

50:01.257 --> 50:03.091
You said you've only been here
for a little while.

50:06.294 --> 50:07.755
Where you from?

50:07.790 --> 50:11.132
Uh, Iowa.
A town called Waterloo?

50:11.761 --> 50:12.793
You asking me?

50:13.697 --> 50:15.169
No. I'm from Waterloo.

50:15.600 --> 50:17.204
Okay.

50:17.239 --> 50:19.305
Your whole family
move out here for New Life?

50:20.308 --> 50:21.769
No, it's just me.

50:21.804 --> 50:24.310
I wanted to do
some missionary work
before school.

50:24.345 --> 50:25.707
(CHUCKLES)

50:25.742 --> 50:28.149
You're from Iowa,

50:28.184 --> 50:31.449
and you came to Idaho
to do missionary work?

50:31.484 --> 50:33.319
Why aren't you
in Africa or something?

50:33.354 --> 50:35.156
Idaho needs the Word
as much as anywhere else.

50:42.231 --> 50:43.824
Okay, listen.

50:43.859 --> 50:45.463
I know this is fun for you.

50:45.498 --> 50:46.662
You get to travel around,

50:46.697 --> 50:48.301
act superior than
everyone else,

50:49.436 --> 50:50.732
and eventually, you go home,

50:50.767 --> 50:52.866
get some boring job,
have too many kids.

50:52.901 --> 50:53.733
It's God's plan.

50:53.769 --> 50:57.145
But there are
other types of people.

50:57.180 --> 50:58.410
People like Charlie,

50:58.445 --> 51:01.644
for whom this amazing plan
doesn't fit.

51:02.713 --> 51:05.846
So, just stay away from him.

51:05.881 --> 51:07.320
He doesn't need this
right now.

51:09.654 --> 51:11.390
I disagree.

51:11.425 --> 51:14.162
(EXHALES) Excuse me?
Sorry, I just, uh...

51:14.197 --> 51:15.559
He's dying.

51:15.594 --> 51:17.198
He's refusing
to go to the hospital.

51:17.233 --> 51:18.760
What he needs
is spiritual guidance.

51:18.795 --> 51:20.267
And you're gonna
give him that?

51:20.302 --> 51:22.302
No. God will.

51:24.933 --> 51:26.141
I see.

51:45.261 --> 51:47.360
My big brother
did some missionary work
for New Life.

51:49.430 --> 51:50.660
Went to South America.

51:51.465 --> 51:53.630
Oh.
Yeah.

51:53.665 --> 51:54.631
I was the black sheep.

51:54.666 --> 51:57.271
I refused to go to church
ever since I was 12.

51:58.307 --> 51:59.702
Dad knew
I was a lost cause,

52:02.245 --> 52:06.247
but not my brother,
he loved New Life.

52:06.282 --> 52:08.348
He wrote me a letter
a few months after he left,

52:08.383 --> 52:10.482
told me he was tired,

52:10.517 --> 52:11.945
and lonely, but he didn't
want to come home

52:11.980 --> 52:13.419
because he didn't want
to get married.

52:14.455 --> 52:15.619
He didn't want to get married?

52:15.654 --> 52:17.423
Dad had set it all up.

52:17.458 --> 52:18.424
Pushed him
into getting married

52:18.459 --> 52:21.823
to this girl from the church
he barely knew.

52:21.858 --> 52:24.397
But when he came back,
he met someone else.

52:24.432 --> 52:26.432
Fell in love,
started a whole new life.

52:26.467 --> 52:29.501
And Dad kicked him out
of the church.

52:30.405 --> 52:31.437
And the family.

52:33.309 --> 52:34.539
I thought he was gonna be able

52:34.574 --> 52:36.607
to get over
all that religious stuff,

52:36.642 --> 52:39.907
but it was like a cancer.

52:39.942 --> 52:42.481
He couldn't shake it.

52:42.516 --> 52:44.318
He just caved in on himself,

52:44.353 --> 52:45.781
stopped sleeping,
stopped eating.

52:45.816 --> 52:46.947
Lost a ton of weight.

52:48.654 --> 52:50.522
One night,
he doesn't come home.

52:52.658 --> 52:54.559
Couple weeks later,
this guy is out jogging

52:54.594 --> 52:56.396
on a bike path
near the river in Lewiston,

52:56.431 --> 52:57.991
sees something washed up
on shore,

52:58.026 --> 52:59.828
and that was Alan.

53:02.305 --> 53:04.470
The love of Charlie's life,
and my brother.

53:05.968 --> 53:08.408
Oh.
Yeah. "Oh."

53:08.443 --> 53:10.938
To this day,
my dad won't admit it.

53:10.973 --> 53:13.479
Told the whole congregation
Alan's death was...

53:15.417 --> 53:17.450
just an unfortunate accident.

53:20.081 --> 53:22.851
Denying him to the end.

53:31.862 --> 53:34.830
Look, I know
that you don't trust me.

53:34.865 --> 53:37.503
And I know
that I haven't known him
for very long,

53:37.538 --> 53:40.473
but I really think
that God brought me here,

53:40.508 --> 53:42.673
right when Charlie
needs it the most.

53:42.708 --> 53:45.544
I just want him to be saved,
that's all...
You listen to me!

53:45.579 --> 53:46.908
He doesn't need saving!

53:48.076 --> 53:50.582
In a few days, he's probably
going to be dead,

53:50.617 --> 53:53.046
so what he needs
is for you to leave him alone.

53:53.081 --> 53:54.718
I'm the only one
who can help him.

53:54.753 --> 53:56.049
You understand me?
CHARLIE: Liz.

54:05.027 --> 54:06.565
(LIZ SIGHS)

54:10.098 --> 54:12.835
(CUTLERY CLACKING)

54:18.711 --> 54:20.546
(CHARLIE WHEEZES SOFTLY)

54:22.715 --> 54:24.077
(TV TURNS ON)

54:24.112 --> 54:26.981
You wanna watch some<i> Maury?</i>

54:28.556 --> 54:29.984
Sounds good, right?

54:30.019 --> 54:33.526
(INDISTINCT CHATTER ON TV)

54:33.561 --> 54:35.088
Actually, I got
another night shift tonight.

54:35.123 --> 54:36.727
I better, uh...

54:36.762 --> 54:37.661
You good for the night?

54:39.765 --> 54:42.062
(SMACKS LIPS)
I'll leave the remote here.

54:47.509 --> 54:49.036
(DOOR OPENS)

54:52.811 --> 54:53.843
(DOOR CLOSES)

54:55.913 --> 54:57.385
(LOCK CLICKS)

55:18.738 --> 55:20.100
(GRUNTS SOFTLY)

55:22.676 --> 55:25.138
(LIGHT SWITCH CLICKING)

55:28.209 --> 55:29.483
(SIGHS)

55:36.085 --> 55:37.557
(SIGHS)

55:43.499 --> 55:45.895
(SNIFFING)

55:47.767 --> 55:49.965
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

56:00.780 --> 56:01.779
(DOOR SHUTS)

56:12.121 --> 56:13.494
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

56:13.529 --> 56:14.924
MAN: Gambino's!

56:14.959 --> 56:16.959
Yeah. You can, uh...

56:16.994 --> 56:19.192
MAN: Money in the mailbox,
leave it on the bench.

56:20.503 --> 56:21.799
Yeah. Thanks.

56:23.869 --> 56:24.868
MAN: I'm Dan.

56:27.609 --> 56:28.806
What?

56:28.841 --> 56:31.776
DAN: I just...
My name, it's Dan.

56:33.681 --> 56:36.143
