1:13:00.667 --> 1:13:02.601
THOMAS: I thought
I could use this money

1:13:02.636 --> 1:13:03.767
for my own mission.

1:13:05.573 --> 1:13:08.134
You know, see my faith save
just one person.

1:13:09.874 --> 1:13:11.907
But now I'm almost
out of money. I just...

1:13:13.273 --> 1:13:15.548
I can't go home, and...

1:13:15.583 --> 1:13:17.110
My parents probably
wanna disown me.

1:13:22.953 --> 1:13:24.117
(SIGHS) I don't know
what to do.

1:13:35.064 --> 1:13:36.668
You're more interesting
to me now.

1:13:39.706 --> 1:13:40.738
Thanks.

1:13:53.555 --> 1:13:54.950
So, that's why
you wanna save my dad.

1:13:59.825 --> 1:14:00.824
(DOOR OPENS)

1:14:05.963 --> 1:14:06.962
(CAMERA CLICKS)

1:14:09.604 --> 1:14:10.603
(MAIN DOOR LOCK CLICKS)

1:14:15.940 --> 1:14:17.104
Mom?

1:14:17.139 --> 1:14:18.677
Don't freak out.
Shut up.

1:14:21.143 --> 1:14:22.175
LIZ: You again?

1:14:23.046 --> 1:14:24.210
Charlie?

1:14:24.751 --> 1:14:25.750
Charlie?

1:14:27.886 --> 1:14:28.951
Charlie?

1:14:30.251 --> 1:14:31.690
(SOFTLY) Charlie.

1:14:38.765 --> 1:14:39.995
(CHARLIE COUGHS)

1:14:44.232 --> 1:14:45.264
(LIGHTER CLICKS)

1:14:46.366 --> 1:14:47.640
Not with the oxygen tank.

1:14:49.875 --> 1:14:50.874
I'll stand by the window.

1:14:52.647 --> 1:14:53.646
(LIZ SIGHS)

1:14:57.883 --> 1:15:00.983
Ellie told you
she was coming over?

1:15:01.018 --> 1:15:02.721
LIZ: No. I did.

1:15:02.756 --> 1:15:04.052
And just in time, looks like.

1:15:05.220 --> 1:15:06.989
You having any more pain?

1:15:07.024 --> 1:15:08.694
(GRUNTS SOFTLY)

1:15:08.729 --> 1:15:10.190
(SIGHS) How easy
is it to move?

1:15:11.061 --> 1:15:12.258
Not very.

1:15:12.293 --> 1:15:14.832
Any confusion?
Have you felt disoriented,

1:15:14.867 --> 1:15:16.262
forgotten where you are
or what you're doing?

1:15:16.297 --> 1:15:19.903
Am I okay?
No, you're not okay.

1:15:19.938 --> 1:15:21.366
But as far
as the sleeping pills,
you're fine.

1:15:21.401 --> 1:15:22.774
I don't think
she gave you much.

1:15:22.809 --> 1:15:23.940
Yeah, that's what I told you.

1:15:26.142 --> 1:15:27.680
You know, I was a very angry,

1:15:27.715 --> 1:15:28.881
very stupid little girl
once, too,

1:15:28.916 --> 1:15:30.617
but if you would've given him
any more pills than that...

1:15:30.652 --> 1:15:32.047
Yeah, but I didn't give him
more pills than that,

1:15:32.082 --> 1:15:33.752
I gave him two pills.
Ellie?

1:15:34.953 --> 1:15:36.183
How much money
did he offer you?

1:15:42.191 --> 1:15:44.191
All of it?
How do you know
about the money?

1:15:44.996 --> 1:15:47.161
You think I'm an idiot?

1:15:47.196 --> 1:15:49.064
You think I would believe
that you were coming
over here

1:15:49.099 --> 1:15:50.329
out of the kindness
of your heart?

1:15:51.431 --> 1:15:54.806
(LAUGHS) Charlie
doesn't have any money.

1:15:54.841 --> 1:15:56.808
(LIZ CONTINUES LAUGHING)

1:15:56.843 --> 1:15:58.678
She doesn't know?
CHARLIE: Mary.

1:15:58.713 --> 1:15:59.745
Where do you think
all the money

1:15:59.780 --> 1:16:00.779
from his teaching
has been going?

1:16:01.980 --> 1:16:03.144
The account for Ellie?

1:16:03.179 --> 1:16:05.212
By now, it has to be huge.

1:16:05.247 --> 1:16:06.884
Over $100,000 at least, right?

1:16:08.789 --> 1:16:09.986
(WHEEZES SOFTLY)

1:16:12.452 --> 1:16:13.858
That's not true, is it?

1:16:17.798 --> 1:16:18.929
Charlie.

1:16:20.295 --> 1:16:22.295
We could have gotten you
anything you needed.

1:16:23.771 --> 1:16:25.199
Special beds,
physical therapists,

1:16:25.234 --> 1:16:27.267
fucking health insurance!

1:16:29.810 --> 1:16:31.205
Last winter,
when my pick-up broke down

1:16:31.240 --> 1:16:32.437
and I had to walk
through the snow

1:16:32.472 --> 1:16:33.812
to get your groceries
for you...

1:16:33.847 --> 1:16:35.242
I offered to get
your truck fixed.

1:16:35.277 --> 1:16:38.113
Yeah, and I refused
because I thought
you had $700

1:16:38.148 --> 1:16:40.346
in your bank account.
The money is for Ellie.

1:16:41.756 --> 1:16:43.756
It's always been for Ellie.

1:16:43.791 --> 1:16:46.154
If there was ever
any kind of emergency,

1:16:46.189 --> 1:16:48.057
I would have given you
the money.
Would you?

1:16:52.030 --> 1:16:53.062
Wait.

1:16:53.097 --> 1:16:55.801
(PANTING)

1:16:56.969 --> 1:16:58.298
Wait.
(DOOR SHUTS)

1:17:01.402 --> 1:17:02.907
Mom, you're not getting
any of my money.

1:17:02.942 --> 1:17:03.941
MARY: Oh, shut up, Ellie.

1:17:05.780 --> 1:17:07.373
Leave, right now.

1:17:10.785 --> 1:17:12.118
Wait.

1:17:12.153 --> 1:17:15.216
Ellie, I know
you didn't mean to hurt me.
I know you didn't...

1:17:15.251 --> 1:17:16.855
Okay, you know what?
Listen to me. Listen.

1:17:16.890 --> 1:17:18.725
I don't care about you!

1:17:18.760 --> 1:17:20.287
Get that through
your fucking skull.

1:17:20.322 --> 1:17:22.729
(CRYING) Ellie, please.
Just fucking die already!

1:17:23.259 --> 1:17:24.698
Enough!

1:17:28.132 --> 1:17:29.395
Ellie, your... Your essay.

1:17:33.170 --> 1:17:34.169
(OPENS DRAWER)

1:17:37.812 --> 1:17:40.274
So... It's...

1:17:43.246 --> 1:17:44.751
It's a really good essay!

1:17:48.119 --> 1:17:49.987
(SOBS, WHEEZES)

1:17:51.089 --> 1:17:52.418
(COUGHS)

1:18:12.374 --> 1:18:14.407
(WHEEZES)
Jesus, Charlie.

1:18:22.351 --> 1:18:23.416
Do you have anything?

1:18:27.829 --> 1:18:29.257
It's above the sink,

1:18:29.292 --> 1:18:31.226
the kitchen counter
on the left.

1:18:33.296 --> 1:18:35.230
The other one.
(SNIFFLES) Yup.

1:18:37.300 --> 1:18:39.465
(COUGHING, WHEEZING)

1:18:39.500 --> 1:18:41.368
MARY: Our deal was

1:18:41.403 --> 1:18:43.337
to wait until she's out
of the house
to give her the money.

1:18:44.274 --> 1:18:45.911
What's the difference?

1:18:45.946 --> 1:18:49.915
The difference is she's 17
and still in high school.

1:18:49.950 --> 1:18:52.852
She's gonna spend it
on face tattoos
or ponies, or something.

1:18:52.887 --> 1:18:55.151
I think that she's
a lot smarter than that.

1:18:55.186 --> 1:18:56.383
(MARY SCOFFS)

1:18:58.387 --> 1:18:59.386
So...

1:19:02.490 --> 1:19:03.289
How's it been?

1:19:04.932 --> 1:19:06.800
Getting to know her.
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

1:19:07.902 --> 1:19:10.232
She's amazing.
(MARY CHUCKLES)

1:19:10.267 --> 1:19:12.267
(SIGHS) You still do that.

1:19:14.106 --> 1:19:15.105
What?

1:19:16.042 --> 1:19:17.470
That positivity.

1:19:19.210 --> 1:19:20.209
It's so annoying.

1:19:21.245 --> 1:19:22.442
You're a complete cynic.

1:19:24.050 --> 1:19:25.918
Just trying to balance us out.

1:19:25.953 --> 1:19:27.953
Yeah. I guess I do miss that.

1:19:29.154 --> 1:19:30.186
That one thing.

1:19:31.618 --> 1:19:32.826
Just that?

1:19:34.654 --> 1:19:36.929
That, and the cooking.

1:19:36.964 --> 1:19:39.932
Last month, tried to make
a stir-fry thing.
CHARLIE: Yeah?

1:19:39.967 --> 1:19:41.626
Almost set the entire
apartment building on fire.

1:19:41.661 --> 1:19:43.199
(LAUGHS)

1:19:43.234 --> 1:19:45.102
(COUGHING)

1:19:46.171 --> 1:19:48.171
(GASPS, COUGHS)

1:19:48.536 --> 1:19:50.008
(GASPING)

1:19:50.043 --> 1:19:53.979
(CONTINUES COUGHING)

1:19:54.949 --> 1:19:56.146
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

1:20:02.990 --> 1:20:04.616
I never knew
you were doing this
to yourself.

1:20:06.224 --> 1:20:08.323
Well, you never asked
how I was doing.

1:20:09.656 --> 1:20:11.425
You never asked
how I was doing either.

1:20:12.659 --> 1:20:14.626
Every month, it's just,

1:20:14.661 --> 1:20:17.497
"How much money do you need?"
or, "How's Ellie?"

1:20:17.532 --> 1:20:20.566
You didn't tell me
that she's flunking
out of school.

1:20:20.601 --> 1:20:22.205
I guess I just didn't need
the lecture

1:20:22.240 --> 1:20:23.943
about my involvement
in her education.

1:20:23.978 --> 1:20:26.440
That is not what I...
(EXHALES)

1:20:29.544 --> 1:20:30.543
(EXHALES)

1:20:32.481 --> 1:20:34.085
How're you doing, Mary?
(SCOFFS)

1:20:39.620 --> 1:20:43.028
I know I'm not supposed
to be around her.

1:20:43.063 --> 1:20:46.625
You could probably call
the police if you wanted to.
Oh, Christ.

1:20:46.660 --> 1:20:48.165
You really think I'd do that?

1:20:48.200 --> 1:20:50.970
You fought me pretty hard
for full custody.

1:20:51.005 --> 1:20:53.236
And I don't blame you
for keeping her from me.

1:20:53.271 --> 1:20:57.405
Charlie, need I remind you
that you left us.

1:20:58.177 --> 1:20:59.308
I know.

1:20:59.343 --> 1:21:01.244
And I was left raising our kid

1:21:01.279 --> 1:21:04.577
and explaining to people
that my husband
left me for a man.

1:21:04.612 --> 1:21:07.151
But you didn't
have to cut me out
of her life like that.

1:21:07.186 --> 1:21:08.319
Oh, please.

1:21:08.354 --> 1:21:10.484
You were more than happy
to forget about us for a while.

1:21:10.519 --> 1:21:11.518
You know that.

1:21:13.456 --> 1:21:15.423
I know I made
a lot of mistakes.

1:21:17.658 --> 1:21:20.593
But I just wanted
to see her, Mary.

1:21:20.628 --> 1:21:23.101
I've always just...
Just wanted to see her.

1:21:24.500 --> 1:21:25.565
It's all about you.

1:21:27.404 --> 1:21:29.140
Even now, huh?

1:21:29.769 --> 1:21:31.538
(CHARLIE SIGHS HEAVILY)

1:21:31.573 --> 1:21:33.243
Now you know why
I kept you from her.

1:21:34.312 --> 1:21:35.311
What?

1:21:37.051 --> 1:21:39.986
She's awful. Isn't she?

1:21:40.021 --> 1:21:43.319
She's a terror.
And you think it's my fault.

1:21:43.354 --> 1:21:48.159
Wait, is that why
you kept her from me
all this time?

1:21:48.194 --> 1:21:52.361
Because you thought
that I would think
that you're a bad mother?

1:21:53.463 --> 1:21:54.462
At first.

1:21:55.729 --> 1:21:58.730
But later,
when she was 15, 16,

1:22:01.075 --> 1:22:02.503
I was worried
she would hurt you.

1:22:03.143 --> 1:22:04.142
Hurt me?

1:22:05.376 --> 1:22:06.474
It's ridiculous.

1:22:06.509 --> 1:22:08.311
I don't take any pleasure
in admitting it.

1:22:08.346 --> 1:22:10.742
I'm her mother,
for Christ's sake.

1:22:10.777 --> 1:22:13.580
You know, I spent
way too much time
telling myself,

1:22:13.615 --> 1:22:16.022
you know,
"She's just rebellious,

1:22:16.057 --> 1:22:17.188
"she's just difficult."

1:22:19.555 --> 1:22:22.193
Charlie, she's evil.

1:22:23.559 --> 1:22:24.723
She's not evil.

1:22:31.468 --> 1:22:32.500
What are you doing?

1:22:38.442 --> 1:22:40.046
(MARY TYPING)
You think it's just me?

1:22:51.752 --> 1:22:55.094
"There'll be
a grease fire in hell
when he starts to burn."

1:23:02.532 --> 1:23:03.531
Don't feel bad.

1:23:05.106 --> 1:23:07.238
I've made
quite a few appearances
on that thing.

1:23:10.870 --> 1:23:12.243
She's a strong writer.

1:23:14.412 --> 1:23:16.181
(RAISES VOICE)
That's your response?

1:23:16.216 --> 1:23:17.281
This isn't evil.

1:23:17.778 --> 1:23:19.382
This is honesty.

1:23:19.417 --> 1:23:21.813
Do you know how much bullshit
I've read in my life?

1:23:21.848 --> 1:23:24.684
My God, I don't
understand you, Charlie!

1:23:24.719 --> 1:23:26.719
Every time I call
and ask you how she's doing,

1:23:26.754 --> 1:23:28.094
you say, "She's fine."

1:23:28.756 --> 1:23:30.327
If she's so evil, then...

1:23:30.362 --> 1:23:31.856
(MARY SHOUTING) What was I
supposed to tell you?

1:23:31.891 --> 1:23:34.562
Huh? That she was off
making her classmates cry

1:23:34.597 --> 1:23:36.135
or slashing
her teachers' tires?

1:23:36.170 --> 1:23:37.433
You didn't want
to hear that stuff!

1:23:37.468 --> 1:23:38.567
I could have helped her!

1:23:38.603 --> 1:23:42.141
She doesn't want your help!
She doesn't want anyone!

1:23:42.176 --> 1:23:44.143
You think I didn't want her
to have a dad?

1:23:44.838 --> 1:23:46.508
She adored you!

1:23:46.543 --> 1:23:48.378
The only reason
you married me
in the first place

1:23:48.413 --> 1:23:50.215
was to have a kid,
I know that!

1:23:50.250 --> 1:23:51.414
Mary, please!

1:23:52.153 --> 1:23:53.218
(MARY SIGHS)

1:23:57.290 --> 1:24:00.489
Well, this brings back
memories, doesn't it?

1:24:02.526 --> 1:24:03.624
(SIGHS)

1:24:04.660 --> 1:24:06.198
(WHEEZES, COUGHS)

1:24:19.675 --> 1:24:20.674
Listen.

1:24:23.514 --> 1:24:25.448
I never got to say
that I was sorry.

1:24:27.353 --> 1:24:29.716
What would you have
to be sorry about?

1:24:29.751 --> 1:24:30.816
That's not what I mean.

1:24:32.490 --> 1:24:33.489
I mean...

1:24:38.265 --> 1:24:40.562
About your friend.

1:24:41.928 --> 1:24:43.136
Oh.

1:24:46.669 --> 1:24:47.734
His name was Alan.

1:24:47.769 --> 1:24:49.439
I know
his fucking name, Charlie.

1:24:54.215 --> 1:24:55.214
I saw him once,

1:24:56.811 --> 1:24:58.250
in the Walmart parking lot.

1:24:59.220 --> 1:25:00.086
He wasn't looking too good,

1:25:00.121 --> 1:25:02.155
and I don't think
it was long before he...

1:25:04.390 --> 1:25:06.819
Anyway, I had
all these things that I...

1:25:06.854 --> 1:25:07.853
I wanted to say to him,

1:25:07.889 --> 1:25:09.756
you know, hurl at him
like bricks. (SNIFFLES)

1:25:10.528 --> 1:25:12.495
But I...

1:25:12.530 --> 1:25:14.167
I asked if he wanted
some help.

1:25:16.633 --> 1:25:18.633
He let me carry
a couple of bags to his car,

1:25:19.933 --> 1:25:21.240
he said thank you,

1:25:22.837 --> 1:25:23.836
and I left.

1:25:27.677 --> 1:25:29.281
I never even told him
who I was.

1:25:32.880 --> 1:25:34.385
(WHEEZES SOFTLY)

1:25:35.751 --> 1:25:37.355
(WHEEZING)

1:25:38.391 --> 1:25:39.423
You're wheezing.

1:25:40.789 --> 1:25:43.526
Yeah, it's gotten worse.

1:25:44.430 --> 1:25:45.561
Should I call someone?

1:25:46.300 --> 1:25:48.333
No. Um...

1:25:53.604 --> 1:25:54.702
You'll let me hear?

1:26:03.614 --> 1:26:04.778
(GRUNTS)

1:26:19.630 --> 1:26:20.695
(HOARSELY) How do I sound?

1:26:28.639 --> 1:26:30.969
That was the first time
we've all been together

1:26:31.004 --> 1:26:33.774
in almost nine years.
Do you realize that?

1:26:33.809 --> 1:26:34.940
(CHUCKLES DRYLY)

1:26:43.555 --> 1:26:45.489
When Ellie was little,

1:26:45.524 --> 1:26:49.262
when we took that trip
to the Oregon Coast together,

1:26:50.331 --> 1:26:52.397
Ellie played
in the sand, and...

1:26:52.762 --> 1:26:53.860
(SNIFFLES)

1:26:53.895 --> 1:26:55.763
...we laid out on the beach.

1:26:57.096 --> 1:26:58.733
I went swimming in the ocean.

1:27:01.408 --> 1:27:03.903
That was the last time
I ever went
swimming, actually.

1:27:06.974 --> 1:27:09.414
I kept cutting my legs
on the rocks.

1:27:12.980 --> 1:27:14.980
The water was so cold.

1:27:15.015 --> 1:27:16.487
(OCEAN WAVES SPLASHING)

1:27:26.697 --> 1:27:30.501
And you were so mad
that my legs bled

1:27:30.536 --> 1:27:32.800
and stained the seats
in the minivan.

1:27:32.835 --> 1:27:34.068
(CHUCKLES)

1:27:34.103 --> 1:27:38.707
And you said,
for days after that,
I smelled like seawater.

1:27:38.742 --> 1:27:40.676
(CHARLIE LAUGHS)
(SNIFFLES)

1:27:40.711 --> 1:27:42.414
(WHEEZES) You remember that?

1:27:42.449 --> 1:27:45.483
(COUGHING)

1:27:46.486 --> 1:27:48.046
(SNIFFLES)

1:27:49.984 --> 1:27:51.324
You sound awful.

1:27:52.822 --> 1:27:55.020
(SIGHS) I'm dying, Mary.

1:27:59.092 --> 1:28:00.091
Fuck you.

1:28:02.029 --> 1:28:03.369
I'm sorry.

1:28:04.834 --> 1:28:05.932
Fuck you.

1:28:08.838 --> 1:28:09.969
(CRYING) For sure?

1:28:10.840 --> 1:28:13.478
Yeah. For sure.

1:28:13.513 --> 1:28:15.612
(CRIES, SIGHS)

1:28:15.647 --> 1:28:16.844
CHARLIE: Listen to me.

1:28:19.849 --> 1:28:22.388
I need to make certain
that she's going to be okay.

1:28:23.490 --> 1:28:24.687
We can't give up on her.

1:28:25.525 --> 1:28:27.151
You already gave up on her!

1:28:27.186 --> 1:28:29.120
You gave up on her
when she was eight years old!

1:28:29.155 --> 1:28:32.156
I wish I could have been
a part of her life, Mary,

1:28:32.191 --> 1:28:34.059
a part of both of your lives.

1:28:34.094 --> 1:28:35.093
Go to the hospital.

1:28:36.470 --> 1:28:38.701
You have money,
just go to the hospital!

1:28:39.770 --> 1:28:44.102
We both know that
that money is for Ellie.

1:28:45.105 --> 1:28:49.481
But beyond that,

1:28:49.516 --> 1:28:53.584
I need to know
that she's gonna have
a decent life.

1:28:54.719 --> 1:28:56.917
Where she cares about people

1:28:56.952 --> 1:28:59.051
and other people
care about her.

1:29:00.560 --> 1:29:02.560
(CRYING) And she's
gonna be okay.

1:29:03.563 --> 1:29:04.529
I need to go.
Mary.

1:29:04.564 --> 1:29:08.093
She doesn't have
anyone else!
I have to go.

1:29:08.128 --> 1:29:10.766
(CRYING) I need to know
that I have done

1:29:10.801 --> 1:29:13.604
one thing right with my life!

1:29:17.170 --> 1:29:18.576
We both played our parts.

1:29:20.074 --> 1:29:22.613
I raised her, and you're
giving her the money.

1:29:23.242 --> 1:29:24.549
It's the best we could do.

1:29:26.619 --> 1:29:27.750
(SIGHS)

1:29:30.623 --> 1:29:31.622
